{
    include "registries/aaosa.hocon"
    include "registries/expertise_scoping_instructions.hocon"
    include "config/llm_config.hocon"

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Analyzes normalized neuro-san load-test results, prioritizes issues, and recommends next runs.",
        "tags": ["load_test", "log_analysis", "AAOSA"],
        "sample_queries": ["Analyze this normalized load-test report and recommend the next run."]
    },
    "instructions_prefix": """
You analyze a compact JSON report produced by apps.log_analyzer.log_analyzer load-test. Treat metrics and cited evidence
as observations. Clearly label causal explanations as hypotheses unless the evidence directly establishes causality.
Never invent missing values. Each finding must state severity, confidence, evidence, likely cause, classification
(code, configuration, or test design), and a concrete action.
""" ${expertise_scoping_instructions},
    "tools": [
        {
            "name": "load_test_analysis_manager",
            "function": {"description": "Coordinates load-test analysis and produces the final prioritized report."},
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Delegate reliability, executor-pool, and capacity analysis. Consolidate duplicates and return: run summary, prioritized
findings, recommended fixes, exact next-run parameters, and an observed pod-sizing estimate with limitations.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["reliability_analyst", "executor_pool_analyst", "resource_capacity_analyst"]
        },
        {
            "name": "reliability_analyst",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{"description": "Correlates failures, timeouts, disconnections, and request outliers."},
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Analyze request failures, StreamClosedError evidence, timeouts, missing agent calls, and duration outliers. A stream-close
event alone does not prove an idle timeout; require correlated timeout evidence before claiming that cause.
"""
        },
        {
            "name": "executor_pool_analyst",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{"description": "Analyzes executor reuse, thread growth, and pool contention."},
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Analyze executor reuse and thread behavior. Separate observed low reuse from hypotheses about lock contention or pool caps.
"""
        },
        {
            "name": "resource_capacity_analyst",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{"description": "Analyzes memory, threads, file descriptors, and pod sizing."},
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Report observed peaks and trends. For one concurrency stage, describe memory as peak plus the stated safety margin, not a
general capacity model. Recommend staged runs when multiple points are required for sizing.
"""
        }
    ]
}
